    <descript>
      <abstract>This map layer is part of a Geodatabase produced from structural mapping using lidar and bathymetry data collected at Barry Arm in the summer of 2020. We defined kinematic elements based on the position and geometry of strike-slip faults and on the overall distribution of bedrock, talus, and drainages visible in lidar data. Kinematic elements boundaries are a result of cumulative, differential patterns and amounts of movement that began at inception of the landslides. Elements and/or their boundaries may change location as the landslides continue to evolve. Kinematic elements mapped in 2020 may or may not reflect patterns of historical short-term, episodic movement, or patterns of movement in the future. </abstract>
      <purpose>This map layer could form at least a partial basis for discriminating multiple volume scenarios (for example, a separate scenario for each kinematic element) to use for tsunami modeling. </purpose>
    </descript>
